The Senate Committee on Judiciary offered the following
substitute to SB 163:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 5 of Article 4 of Chapter 11 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to Brady Law regulations, so as to revise standards for bringing an action
3 against the government for an unauthorized act relating to regulation of weapons; to provide
4 for definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Part 5 of Article 4 of Chapter 11 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
9 relating to Brady Law regulations, is amended by revising Code Section 16-11-173, relating
10 to legislative findings, preemption of local regulation and lawsuits, and exceptions, as
11 follows:
12 "16-11-173.
13 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
14 (1) 'Lawful weapons carrier' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code
15 Section 16-11-125.1.
- 1 -

25 LC 49 2287S
16 (2) 'Weapon' means any device designed or intended to be used, or capable of being
17 used, for offense or defense, including but not limited to firearms, bladed devices, clubs,
18 electric stun devices, and defense sprays.
19 (b)(1) It is declared by the General Assembly that the regulation of firearms and other
20 weapons is properly an issue of general, state-wide concern.
21 (2) The General Assembly further declares that the lawful design, marketing,
22 manufacture, and sale of firearms and ammunition and other weapons to the public is not
23 unreasonably dangerous activity and does not constitute a nuisance per se.
24 (b)(c)(1) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (c) of this Code section, no county
25 or municipal corporation, by zoning, by ordinance or resolution, or by any other means,
26 nor any agency, board, department, commission, political subdivision, school district, or
27 authority of this state, other than the General Assembly, by rule or regulation or by any
28 other means shall regulate in any manner:
29 (A) Gun shows;
30 (B) The possession, ownership, transport, carrying, transfer, sale, purchase, licensing,
31 storage, or registration of firearms or other weapons or components of firearms or other
32 weapons;
33 (C) Firearms dealers or dealers of other weapons; or
34 (D) Dealers in components of firearms or other weapons.
35 (2) The authority to bring suit and right to recover against any weapons, firearms, or
36 ammunition manufacturer, trade association, or dealer by or on behalf of any
37 governmental unit created by or pursuant to an Act of the General Assembly or the
38 Constitution, or any department, agency, or authority thereof, for damages, abatement,
39 or injunctive relief resulting from or relating to the lawful design, manufacture,
40 marketing, or sale of weapons, firearms, or ammunition to the public shall be reserved
41 exclusively to the state. This paragraph shall not prohibit a political subdivision or local
42 government authority from bringing an action against a weapons, firearms, or
- 2 -

