68 (f) As used in this Code section, the term 'weapon' means any device designed or intended
69 to be used, or capable of being used, for offense or defense, including but not limited to
70 firearms, bladed devices, clubs, electric stun devices, and defense sprays.
71 (g) Any person aggrieved as a result of a violation of this Code section may bring an
72 action against the person who caused such aggrievement. The aggrieved person shall be
73 entitled to reasonable attorney's fees and expenses of litigation and may recover or obtain
74 against the person who caused such damages any of the following:
75 (1) Actual damages or $100.00, whichever is greater;
76 (2) Equitable relief, including, but not limited to, an injunction or restitution of money
77 and property; and
78 (3) Any other relief which the court deems proper Any individual who is a lawful
79 weapons carrier who is or has been subject to an act, rule, regulation, ordinance, or
80 resolution in violation of this Code section shall have standing to bring:
81 (1) An action in mandamus or other legal proceeding against a public entity or public
82 officer in his or her official capacity to obtain declaratory or injunctive relief. A
83 prevailing plaintiff in such action shall be entitled to recover his or her costs in such
84 action, including reasonable attorney's fees; or
85 (2) A civil action when such individual suffers personal, property, or economic damage
86 and recover the greater of:
87 (A) Actual damages or $50,000.00, whichever is greater, plus the expenses of litigation
88 and reasonable attorney's fees; or
89 (B) Liquidated damages of three times the expenses of litigation and reasonable
90 attorney's fees.
91 (h) Any action brought pursuant to this Code section shall be brought in the superior court
92 of the county in which the violation occurred and within one year of such violation."
93 SECTION 2.
